
Running the sample app:

$ git clone git@github.com:dozed/fink.git
$ cd fink
$ mvn clean package
$ mvn -P jetty compile

The sample application is running on: http://localhost:8080/
The admin panel is reachable under: http://localhost:8080/fink-admin/ (<- note the extra / at the end)


Rapid development:

Here are some tipps to make development more productive. Basically they allow you to work on your codebase
without having to redeploy the web application each time.

- You can edit the web resources in fink-admin/src/main/webapp and fink-sample/src/main/webapp. Both folders are mounted to the webroot.

- For rapid development JRebel is also great. It can detect changes in .class files and
  reload those classes on the-fly.


Using JRebel:

- Install JRebel
- Create configuration

  $ cd fink/fink-sample
  $ mvn -P jrebel jrebel:generate -Drebel.xml.dir=src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/classes

- Edit configuration:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<application xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="http://www.zeroturnaround.com" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.zeroturnaround.com http://www.zeroturnaround.com/alderaan/rebel-2_0.xsd">
  <classpath>
    <dir name="/home/stefan/Desktop/fink/fink-sample/target/fink-sample-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT/WEB-INF/classes" />
    <dir name="/home/stefan/Desktop/fink/fink-admin/target/fink-admin-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT/WEB-INF/classes" />
    <dir name="/home/stefan/Desktop/fink/fink-data/target/classes" />
  </classpath>
</application>

- Activate JRebel:

  $ export MAVEN_OPTS="-javaagent:$JREBEL_HOME/jrebel.jar -Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m"
  

Eclipse related:

If you use Eclipse as IDE, it is suggested to run "mvn eclipse:eclipse" before importing the projects to eclipse.
This is to prevent problems with AspectJ.


Using the quickstart archetype:

The following command creates a simple fink-based website. 

$ mvn archetype:generate \
  -DarchetypeGroupId=org.noorg.fink \
  -DarchetypeArtifactId=website-quickstart \
  -DarchetypeVersion=0.0.1-SNAPSHOT \
  -DgroupId=org.fooorg \
  -DartifactId=website


